### Skill `factory-pipelines`

```markdown
# Pipeline Management

Pipelines are deterministic, linear sequences of stages.
Unlike channels (open debate), pipelines enforce strict sequential execution.

## Stage types
- **script**: Runs a bash script directly. No LLM. Fast and deterministic.
- **agent**: Delegates to an agent with a prompt. Uses LLM reasoning.

## Create a pipeline
manage_factory(entity: "pipelines", action: "upsert", id: "my-pipeline", params: {
  name: "My Pipeline",
  description: "What it does",
  stages: [
    { id: "lint", name: "Lint", type: "script", script: "lint.sh", timeoutMs: 60000 },
    { id: "review", name: "Review", type: "agent", agentId: "code-reviewer",
      prompt: "Review lint results: {{stages.lint.output}}" }
  ],
  scripts: {
    "lint.sh": "#!/bin/bash\npnpm lint && echo '---OUTPUT---\n{\"passed\":true}\n---END OUTPUT---'"
  }
})

## Run a pipeline (fire-and-forget)
run_pipeline(pipelineId: "my-pipeline")
# → { runId: "run_abc123" }

## Check run status
manage_factory(entity: "pipelines", action: "get", id: "my-pipeline/runs/run_abc123")

## List all pipelines
manage_factory(entity: "pipelines", action: "get")

## List runs for a pipeline
manage_factory(entity: "pipelines", action: "get", id: "my-pipeline/runs")
```

